Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper discusses a security vulnerability in the encryption scheme of the Moscow Internet voting system. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also likely as the paper discusses the potential impact of the security vulnerability on the election process. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper discusses the implementation of the encryption scheme in the voting system. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper discusses how the security vulnerability can be potentially used for vote counting. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the semantic security of the ElGamal encryption system.
